cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents new algorithms for computing all-pairs shortest paths. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the algorithms can be used for spatial and temporal reasoning, which is relevant to the planning and scheduling community. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possibility as the algorithms make use of graph separators and chordal graphs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents empirical results comparing the performance of the algorithms to existing state-of-the-art algorithms. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithms in terms of their time complexity.
